Trollbot v1.0 Installation Instructions
---------------------------------------

Trollbot uses the GNU Build System.


Simple Install:

./configure
make
make install

This should be enough for most users, it will install all required
files to trollbot/ in your home directory.

Advanced Install:
  --prefix=PREFIX          install files to PREFIX (ex: /home/poutine/clowns)
  --with-tclconfig=PATH    use tclConfig.sh from PATH
                           (configure gets Tcl configuration from here)
  --with-tcl=PATH          use Tcl from PATH
  --with-tclsh=TCLSH       use TCLSH as the tclsh program
                           (let configure find Tcl using this program)
  --with-php-cflags=FLAGS  CFLAGS to use for PHP
  --with-php-ldflags=FLAGS LDFLAGS to use PHP
  --with-php-config=PATH   use php-config from PATH
  --with-php-lib=PATH      PATH to libphp5.so or libphp4.so
  --with-php=(4|5)         configure with PHP4 or 5 support
  --with-perl=PATH         use Perl from PATH


Trollbot can use the libphp4.so or libphp5.so that Apache uses. To use
it you usually have to specify these configure flags.

For PHP 5
./configure --with-php=5 --with-php-config=/usr/local/bin --with-php-lib=/usr/local/apache2/modules

For PHP 4
./configure --with-php=4 --with-php-config=/usr/local/bin --with-php-lib=/usr/local/apache2/modules
